public class WorldPlace extends com.telenav.mesakit.graph.Place
An place in a WorldGraph, scoped by a WorldCell and having a WorldPlaceIdentifier. The cell for this graph element can be retrieved with worldCell() and an override of the identifier() method from Place returns the WorldPlaceIdentifier for the place.

World places are unlike other graph elements in a world graph in that they contain their own data (name, location, population and type). Global spatial queries of places in WorldGraphIndex retrieve this information more efficiently than having it be retrieved from sub-graphs.

Note that there are two methods to retrieve the graph of this GraphElement. The GraphElement.graph() method overrides GraphElement.graph() to return the WorldGraph that contains this element, while the subgraph() method returns the graph where the element is actually stored (the cell sub-graph of the world graph).
